Pelvic organ prolapse occurs when tissue in the womb becomes weak . 
 Many who suffer the painful condition are only offered hysterectomies . 
 But the surgical removal of reproductive organs ends fertility in patients . 
 Now one gynaecologist claims thousands undergo operation needlessly . 
 Jonathan Broome says more should be offered half-hour key hole surgery . 
 Sacrohysteropexy uses a sling to lift and hold the womb back in place . 
 